Fig. 5
); postpronotal, pre-sutural, spal area, intraalar area and area after the M-mark silvery-grey pollinose. Scutellum with brownish mark, apical scutellar area yellowish (
Fig. 5
). Acr 3 : 4 , unordered. Dc 2 : 3 . Pprn 2 , developed and 2 weak. Pra 2 , slightly differentiated and subequal in length, seta near suture more dorsal. Prepm with weak ground setulae. Pre-basal scutellar area with short ground setulae. Subapical scutellar setae 2 pairs. Discal scutellar setae 1 pair. Discal area with short and weak setae. Lateral scutellar setae present.
